INSERT INTO `wp_options` VALUES(247, 0, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2011/11/01/matt-mitchell-digital-subscriptions-to-your-content/'' title=''Online content creators struggle to monetize their content effectively with a pure advertising model. At MediaPass we’ve helped hundreds of publishers sell subscriptions to their online content, giving us a unique expertise in digital subscriptions. The subject of online paywalls is very topical right now. Unfortunately, however, there’s a lot of speculation [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Matt Mitchell: Digital Subscriptions to Your Content</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/akot2ayZP90/joost-de-valk-answers-questions-from-his-peers'' title=''When do you think that WordPress is going to completely rewrite their code base so it’s an actual CMS instead of a hacked together glorified blogging system? I find I get that question quite a lot and it annoys me. WordPress is being rewritten all the time. Check out the development that happens on Trac. Most of the people who ask questions like that haven’t [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: Joost de Valk Answers Questions From His Peers</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/hzPgWxMpCOU/have-you-ever-kvetched'' title=''It’s been a long time since I’ve visited the Kvetch page on WordPress.org but recently, I discovered that the page loads a random Kvetch that was submitted by a user upon each page load. Think of this form as an anonymous way to complain or get something off your chest related to WordPress. Now, I’ve never submitted anything to this form before but from relo [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: Have You Ever Kvetched?</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2011/11/01/peter-chester-170-radio-stations-wordpress-at-scale/'' title=''We launched over 170 sites in 4 months starting from scratch. In this session, I will give an overview of what’s involved in producing and launching a high traffic (many million uniques per month) network of WordPress blogs. Architecting for scale Coding practices Performance tuning Launching [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Peter Chester: 170 Radio Stations: WordPress at Scale</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/227FWrJxvWI/'' title=''Magazzino is a minimalist professional theme with sidebar and footer widgets. REProsumer is a 3-column widgetized theme. [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 11/1</a></li></ul></div>', 'no');
